17:39.467 --> 17:41.467
So please
update your stereotypes

17:41.467 --> 17:43.567
about the University
of Mississippi,

17:43.567 --> 17:45.967
which I believe
is the official slogan

17:45.967 --> 17:48.600
of the University
of Mississippi.

17:48.600 --> 17:50.767
And while researchers
wait for marijuana

17:50.767 --> 17:52.800
to study whether it
helps with PTSD,

17:52.800 --> 17:54.700
plenty of
veterans will tell you,

17:54.700 --> 17:56.433
it absolutely does.

17:56.433 --> 17:57.867
Take Danny Belcher.

17:57.867 --> 17:59.834
He's a Vietnam vet
who'd been prescribed

17:59.834 --> 18:02.000
a great deal of medication
for pain and depression,

18:02.000 --> 18:04.934
but, as he told the
Kentucky legislature in 2014,

18:04.934 --> 18:06.767
he found that
when he tried marijuana,

18:06.767 --> 18:08.867
it started really helping him.

18:08.867 --> 18:11.500
- I do have my bowl of pot
in my house,

18:11.500 --> 18:13.867
and if I wake up at night
and had a nightmare,

18:13.867 --> 18:16.300
when I'm
wringing wet with sweat...

18:21.767 --> 18:24.233
and I see Kramer,
his dead body,

18:24.233 --> 18:26.400
Rodriguez, his dead body...

18:26.400 --> 18:29.767
If that nightmare gets so bad
I can't wake up

18:29.767 --> 18:32.066
and realize it's
just a nightmare,

18:32.066 --> 18:35.533
I will light that pipe up,
I'll be a criminal,

18:35.533 --> 18:37.200
I'll go back to sleep.

18:37.200 --> 18:41.633
But next morning, I will get up
at 6:00 like I always do,

18:41.633 --> 18:44.500
my four days a week
I go to the gym, I run.

18:44.500 --> 18:46.567
I help other veterans.

18:46.567 --> 18:49.834
I couldn't do that if I was on
the damn drugs the VA had me on.

18:49.834 --> 18:51.333
- Exactly.

18:51.333 --> 18:53.300
So for all the talk
you hear of marijuana

18:53.300 --> 18:55.233
being a "gateway drug,"
in his case,

18:55.233 --> 18:57.100
that gateway
led to peaceful sleep,

18:57.100 --> 18:59.834
rigorous exercise,
and community service.

18:59.834 --> 19:02.233
Pretty nice fucking gate
