19:13.233 --> 19:17.300
But the shortcomings of that
law touch on many of the reasons

19:17.300 --> 19:18.767
why "legal marijuana"

19:18.767 --> 19:21.166
can actually be
a bit of a gray area.

19:21.166 --> 19:23.333
For a start, Kentucky's law
has many restrictions.

19:23.333 --> 19:25.600
It only applies
to one marijuana product,

19:25.600 --> 19:28.967
and it requires a written order,
or a prescription,

19:28.967 --> 19:30.700
and that is a real problem.

19:30.700 --> 19:33.400
Because under federal law,
it is technically illegal

19:33.400 --> 19:36.433
for any doctor to write you
a prescription for marijuana.

19:36.433 --> 19:39.467
Now so most states, they get
around that by just calling

19:39.467 --> 19:41.333
for a recommendation
or certification,

19:41.333 --> 19:42.767
which doctors can give you.

19:42.767 --> 19:45.033
But even if Kentucky's
law did that,

19:45.033 --> 19:47.633
if Danny went to his
doctors at the VA,

19:47.633 --> 19:49.033
they couldn't
give him anything,

19:49.033 --> 19:51.033
because they're
a federal hospital.

19:51.033 --> 19:53.400
And federal policy
prohibits VA doctors

19:53.400 --> 19:55.166
from even recommending
marijuana,

19:55.166 --> 19:56.834
regardless of state law

19:56.834 --> 19:58.667
and regardless
of their medical opinion,

19:58.667 --> 20:00.533
which again is a bit weird.

20:00.533 --> 20:03.433
A doctor shouldn't be ignored
because he recommends marijuana.

20:03.433 --> 20:06.433
A doctor should only be ignored
because he's televised.

20:06.433 --> 20:08.000
We all agree on that.

20:08.000 --> 20:11.200
We're all on the same page
on that one, I think.

20:11.200 --> 20:12.300
[cheers and applause]

20:12.300 --> 20:14.867
But here's the thing,
it gets worse.

20:14.867 --> 20:16.800
Even if Danny
had a private doctor,

20:16.800 --> 20:18.700
and Kentucky rewrote its law,

20:18.700 --> 20:20.667
where would he get
marijuana from?

20:20.667 --> 20:23.633
Because Kentucky's law also
neglected to set up any system

20:23.633 --> 20:25.667
for legal marijuana
distribution.

20:25.667 --> 20:28.266
So he'd have to obtain it
from somewhere else.

20:28.266 --> 20:30.767
But where would he do that,
and how?

20:30.767 --> 20:32.500
Now he could have it shipped,
right?

20:32.500 --> 20:33.767
Except, no.

20:33.767 --> 20:35.333
That would be a federal crime.

20:35.333 --> 20:36.734
But what if he flew to a state

20:36.734 --> 20:38.567
where marijuana is
completely legal,

20:38.567 --> 20:40.400
and just brought it back
to Kentucky?

20:40.400 --> 20:41.633
Here's the thing, no again.

20:41.633 --> 20:43.266
That is also a federal crime.

20:43.266 --> 20:45.066
Could he drive
to a neighboring state

20:45.066 --> 20:46.266
to get what he needs?

20:46.266 --> 20:48.667
Unfortunately, no,
because two of those states

20:48.667 --> 20:50.533
have total
prohibitions on marijuana,

20:50.533 --> 20:53.567
and the rest don't currently
